---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import avatarImage from "../../public/diego-francisco-concepcion.webp";
---

<Layout
	title="Diego | Android Developer & Tech Enthusiast"
	description="Android & Backend developer with 10+ years of experience. I write about coding, home automation, and my homelab experiments."
>
	<section
		class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:items-start gap-12 md:mt-10"
	>
		<div
			class="flex-shrink-0 relative order-first md:order-last w-64 h-64 lg:w-96 lg:h-96 max-w-sm md:w-80 md:h-80"
		>
			<div
				class="absolute inset-0 bg-ink translate-x-4 translate-y-4 rounded-full"
			>
			</div>
			<Image
				src={avatarImage}
				width={320}
				height={320}
				alt="Diego Francisco ConcepciÃ³n"
				class="relative w-full h-full border-4 border-brutal object-cover transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105 hover:rotate-3 hover:shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_var(--color-primary)] rounded-full"
			/>
		</div>

		<div class="flex-1 space-y-8">
			<h1
				class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black leading-none break-words"
			>
				<span class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground px-2 rounded-lg">Diego</span> Francisco ConcepciÃ³n
			</h1>
			<div class="space-y-4 border-l-8 border-brutal pl-6">
				<p
					class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
				>
					Hi! ðŸ˜Š<br/>I am a developer with over 10 years of experience building
					Android apps. I also have backend experience using Python
					with Django and Flask, and more recently Spring Boot with
					Kotlin. Since I am curious by nature, I have also played
					around with web development using React, Astro, and even
					Vue. On top of that, I have created desktop applications
					using Python with Qt and Java with JavaFX.
				</p>

				<p
					class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
				>
					Beyond coding, I am really passionate about computers. I
					love home automation and use my homelab with Home Assistant
					to automate my daily routines. I also enjoy tinkering with
					services like Pihole, TrueNAS, Immich, and other self hosted
					tools just for learning purposes.
				</p>

				<p
					class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
				>
					Finally, I love technology in general, so I sometimes write
					about it. I even started a podcast back in 2018, way before
					everyone else did. I eventually hung up the mic, so I will
					never know if I was about to hit the jackpot or if I just
					saved the internet from yet another tech podcast.
				</p>

				<p
					class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
				>
					I write about all of this in my blog, plus a lot of other
					things I left out to not sound too geeky.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div
				class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 pt-6 justify-center md:justify-start"
			>
				<a
					href="https://github.com/costular"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					class="brutal-btn bg-ink text-ink-contrast p-4 transition-transform hover:scale-110 hover:rotate-6"
					aria-label="GitHub"
				>
					<svg
						xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
